<TITLE> Former HC judge Abdul Khaliq dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 03 (bdnews24.com)  Former High Court judge Abdul Khaliq died of heart disease at Ibrahim Cardiac Hospital at 12:45pm Thursday. He was 87. Justice Khaliq was admitted to the hospital Tuesday night where his condition worsened, son-in-law AH Mahmud Ali told bdnews24.com. Khaliq's first Janaza will be held at the Supreme Court premises at 3pm and the second at Banani after asr prayers. He will be buried at Banani graveyard. Khaliq was an adviser to the first caretaker government led by Shahabuddin Ahmed in 1991. He was born in 1921 in Sonarai village under Domar Upazila in Nilphamari. The late judge obtained BN degree from the University of Calcutta and joined the then East Pakistan Civil Service in 1947. Khaliq worked as district sessions judge and register of the High Court. He retired in 1986. He also worked as secretary to the provincial assembly from 1956 to 1966 of the then East Pakistan. He was chairman of Administrative Appellate Tribunal and Shishu Hospital Trust. bdnews24
